    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="edition">
                <div type="textpart">
                    <ab>In nomine sanctae et individuae trinitatis. <persName key="#Emperor/king"
                            ref="#people/7">Otto</persName> superna favente clementia Romanorum <rs
                            key="#Emperor/king">imperator</rs> augustus. Si locis divino cultui
                        mancipatis proprietates pertinencias et legum instituta augere defendere et
                        confirmare studuerimus, id non solum humana laude predicandum, verum etiam
                        divina remuneratione nobis recompensandum credimus et vere scimus.
                        Quapropter agnoscant omnes fideles nostri presentes atque futuri, qualiter
                        nos pro dei omnipotentis amore animeque nostrae absolutione nec non
                        interventu ac peticione domni <persName key="#Archbishops"><name ref="Leo"
                                >Leonis</name></persName>
                        <orgName key="#Imperial/royal_diploma #Offersio/donatio #Cities #Rivers #Massae #Penalty #Castle #Tower #Ports #Comitatus #Dioecesis #Teloneum #Rights_of_use_on_woods/pastures/waters #Districtio #Churches #Monasteries" ref="#juridical_persons/1471">sanctae <placeName ref="#places/594"
                                >Rauennatis</placeName> eclesie</orgName> venerabilis <rs
                            key="#Archbishops">archiepiscopi</rs> sue sanctae sedi per hanc nostram
                        preceptalem paginam confirmamus et firmissime corroboramus omnes illo
                        pertinentes episcopatus <rs key="#Monasteries">monasteria</rs> 
                        <rs key="#Churches">eclesias</rs> <rs key="#Cities">civitates</rs> et 
                        <rs key="#Castle">castella</rs> ac omnes
                        res que unquam per cartas antiquas <rs key="#Imperial/royal_diploma">
                            privilegia atque precepta</rs> ad eandem
                        sacrosanctam Rauennatem eclesiam pertinuerunt, insuper ea que in nostri
                        diadematis temporibus vel antea a <persName
                            key="#Popes">Iohanne</persName> <rs key="#Popes">papa</rs> seu a <persName key="#Popes"
                                ref="#people/1636">Gregorio</persName> papa ad ipsam
                        eclesiam sunt oblata et perpetualiter donata et a nobis confirmata,
                        videlicet <rs key="#Comitatus">comitatum</rs> 
                        <geogName key="#Comitatus" ref="#estates/1478"><placeName 
                            key="#Comitatus">Feretanum</placeName></geogName> cum episcopatu suo et cum 
                        <rs key="#Monasteries">monasterio</rs> <orgName key="#Monasteries">sancti
                            Salvatoris</orgName> in ipso comitatu posito, comitatum <placeName key="#Castle" 
                                ref="#places/1890"><geogName key="#Comitatus"
                                ref="#estates/1479">Cesenate</geogName></placeName> cum 
                        <rs key="#Castle">castro vetere et
                        novo</rs> et <rs key="#Tower">turribus</rs> ac omnibus sibi pertinentibus, 
                        comitatum <placeName
                            key="#Rights_of_use_on_woods/pastures/waters" ref="#places/4667"
                            ><geogName key="#Comitatus" ref="#estates/3913"><orgName
                                key="#Dioecesis">Ficloclensem</orgName></geogName></placeName> cum
                        <rs key="#Rights_of_use_on_woods/pastures/waters">ripa</rs> et 
                            episcopatu suo, episcopatum <orgName>Regiensem</orgName> cum dono et consecratione,
                        sicut nos ipsi eclesie per preceptum nostrum in perpetuum confirmavimus et
                        tradidimus, simulque comitatum <placeName
                            key="#Comitatus"><geogName key="#Comitatus" ref="#estates/3987"
                                >Decimanum</geogName></placeName>, comitatum <placeName
                                    key="#Comitatus"><geogName key="#Comitatus" ref="#estates/3988"
                                        >Trauersarie</geogName></placeName>, comitatum
                        <placeName
                            key="#Comitatus" ref="#places/3512"><geogName key="#Comitatus"
                                ref="#estates/2409">Imulensem</geogName></placeName>, comitatum <placeName
                                    key="#Fisheries #Comitatus #Rights_of_use_on_woods/pastures/waters" 
                                    ref="#places/485"><geogName key="#Fisheries #Comitatus #Rights_of_use_on_woods/pastures/waters"
                                        ref="#estates/2449">Cumaclensem</geogName></placeName> cum 
                        <rs key="#Rights_of_use_on_woods/pastures/waters">ripa</rs> et 
                        <rs key="#Fisheries">piscariis</rs> suis, comitatum
                        <placeName
                            key="#Fisheries #Comitatus #Rights_of_use_on_woods/pastures/waters" 
                            ref="#places/80"><geogName key="#Fisheries #Comitatus #Rights_of_use_on_woods/pastures/waters"
                                ref="#estates/84">Ferarie</geogName></placeName> cum ripa et piscariis suis, <rs key="#Massae">massam</rs> que
                        vocatur <geogName key="#Massae" ref="#estates/2479"><placeName
                                ref="#places/4600">Fiscalia</placeName></geogName> cum <placeName
                            ref="#places/3520">Corna cervina</placeName>, <rs key="#Monasteries"
                            >monasterium</rs>
                        <orgName key="#Monasteries" ref="#juridical_persons/1460">sanctae Marie in
                                <placeName ref="#places/4179">Pompusia</placeName></orgName>,
                        monasterium <orgName key="#Monasteries">sancti Ilarii in Galigata</orgName>
                        cum omni <rs key="#Districtio"
                            >districtione placitoque</rs> suo, nec non districtum Rauenne
                        cum portis et ripa muris publicaliis omnibus <rs key="#Teloneum">teloneis</rs> monetam et omnem
                        potestatem in [omnibus] infra et extra civitatem Rauenne, insuper de <rs
                            key="#Ports">portu</rs>
                        <placeName key="#Fisheries #Ports"><geogName key="#Fisheries #Ports"
                                ref="#estates/2457 #estates/2465">Uolane</geogName></placeName> cum
                            <rs key="#Fisheries #Ports">piscariis</rs> suis usque ad portam Ceruie,
                        monasterium <orgName key="#Monasteries">sancti Thome apostoli</orgName> et 
                        <orgName key="#Monasteries" ref="#juridical_persons/3668">sanctae Eufemie</orgName> infra civitatem
                        <placeName ref="#places/1806"
                            >Ariminensem</placeName> cum omnibus pertinentiis eorum 
                        seu omnes res quascumque <rs key="#Deacons">diaconus</rs>
                        <persName key="#Deacons"><name ref="Petrus">Petrus</name></persName> filius 
                        <persName key="#Marquis/duke"><name ref="Martinus">Martini</name></persName> 
                        <rs key="#Marquis/duke">ducis</rs> per <rs key="#Offersio/donatio">cartulam donationis</rs> 
                        in sanctam Rauennatem
                        eclesiam tradidit, et quascumque <persName key="#Countess"><name
                                ref="Ingelrada">Ingelrada</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Countess">comitissa</rs> detinuit, sicuti 
                        <persName
                            key="#Emperor/king" ref="#people/173">avus noster</persName> in placito
                        <persName key="#Archbishops"><name ref="Petrus"
                            >Petro</name></persName> Rauennati archiepiscopo legaliter investivit et in perpetuum
                        confirmavit, itemque omnes res et possessiones quas 
                        <persName><name ref="Lambertus">Lanbertus</name></persName> cum uxore et
                        filiis suis habuerunt a mari usque ad Alpes, a fluvio <placeName
                            key="#Rivers" ref="#places/3548">Reno</placeName> usque ad <placeName
                            key="#Rivers" ref="#places/4609">Folia</placeName>, sicuti nos in
                        prefata eclesia olim tradidimus, quoniam inimici rei publice et sanctae
                        Rauennatis eclesie aperte facti sunt, -- atque hec [omn]ia in omnibus, sicut
                        iam confirmavimus et olim confirmata fuerunt, prefato Leoni archiepiscopo et
                        suis successoribus in perpetuum stabilimus. Unde imperiali statuimus edicto
                        u[t], si aliquis dux marchio comes vicecomes seu ulla imperii nostri magna
                        parvaque persona eandem Rauennatem eclesiam disvestierit seu molestaverit,
                            <rs key="#Penalty">centum libras auri cocti</rs> componat, medietatem
                        <rs key="#Camera_regis">camerae nostrae</rs> ac medietatem 
                        <rs
                            key="#Camera_of_other_public_authorities">prescripto archiepiscopo</rs> Rauennati suis
                        successoribus. Quod ut verius credatur, hanc paginam manu propria
                        corroborantes sigillari precepimus. Signum domni Ottonis caesaris
                        invictissimi. <persName key="#Chancellor"><name
                            ref="Eribertus">Heribertus</name></persName> <rs key="#Chancellor">cancellarius</rs> 
                        vice <persName
                            key="#Bishops"><name ref="Petrus"
                                >Petri</name></persName> Cumani episcopi recognovit.
                        Data V. kal. octob. anno dominice incarnationis DCCCCXCVIIII, indictione
                        XII, anno tercii Ottonis regnantis XVI, imperii IIII; acta <placeName ref="#places/52">Romae</placeName>;
                        feliciter.</ab>
                </div>
            </div>
